Creeping landslide devouring part of Wyoming town
snippet.description: What's happening in this Wyoming resort town might be better described as a land creep than a landslide, but the lack of speed has not hindered the sheer power of the moving earth.

snippet.title: Creeping landslide devouring part of Wyoming town
snippet.description: No one can say precisely when the mountainside collapsing into this Wyoming resort town will give way. But it appears increasingly likely that when it does, it's going to take a piece of Jackson with it.

snippet.title: Looming, creeping landslide splits home in Wyoming
snippet.description: A sudden lurch in a creeping landslide in the northwest Wyoming resort town of Jackson split a house in two and forced workers to abandon just-begun efforts to stabilize the hillside.
